Baking powder is a western thing, also I recommend baking your baking powder (200 degrees for 2 hours) removing the water and turning it from bicarbonate to sodium carbonate which has a lower pH, making your noodles firmer and more yellow. Some add potassium carbonate so as to make the noodles more "slurpable", but the specifics and science of ramen noodles is a matter or some debate. I don't know why he's using 00 flour, usually used for cakes and pastries, which has a lower protein content which would be counter productive.
